Peter,

    RFC 974 is pretty carefully written such that it is impossible,
with any combination of MX preferences, to get mail to loop.  Unless
mailers ignore the recommendations in the RFC I think the worst possible
occurrence is that mail won't get to the host (if someone gets the
meaning of the preferences reversed the messages will be passed in
the reverse direction to the worst MX host).

    If you convince me I'm wrong I'll be very annoyed with myself. :-)

Craig

